It ain't a stack anymore.

05:12.713 --> 05:14.446
Looks more like a pile.

05:14.448 --> 05:16.981
No, no, noooo!

05:16.983 --> 05:19.117
Nice doggy doggy.
Help!

05:19.119 --> 05:20.519
Where is the disarm button?

05:20.521 --> 05:22.054
Granny!

05:22.056 --> 05:23.856
Get back there, get back!

05:23.858 --> 05:25.590
Sorry, granny!

05:25.592 --> 05:27.726
Look, I don't know what you took
from the sheriff,

05:27.728 --> 05:30.462
But whatever it was,
it messed him up big time.

05:30.464 --> 05:33.632
And he needs a friend,
even a shitty friend like you.

05:36.603 --> 05:39.538
Hey, baby.
Whatchu need?

05:39.540 --> 05:41.339
I don't know
how this works,

05:41.341 --> 05:43.275
But I got nothing
to live for,

05:43.277 --> 05:47.145
So I might as well see
a butt and some boobies

05:47.147 --> 05:49.347
At least once
before I die.

05:49.349 --> 05:50.815
$10.

05:50.817 --> 05:55.287
Here, I get 1% cash back
on qualifying purchases.

05:55.289 --> 05:57.622
Ellis!

05:57.624 --> 05:59.023
♪♪

05:59.025 --> 06:00.759
♪ milk, milk, lemonade ♪

06:00.761 --> 06:02.895
♪ around the back,
I get paid ♪

06:02.897 --> 06:04.496
♪ milk, milk, lemonade ♪

06:04.498 --> 06:06.899
♪ around the back,
my money's made ♪

06:06.901 --> 06:09.768
I can't find it, baby.
Where is it?

06:09.770 --> 06:11.303
In my abdomen.

06:11.305 --> 06:13.638
It retracts
when I'm upset.

06:13.640 --> 06:16.441
One virgin
mississippi mud slide.

06:16.443 --> 06:17.842
It's pretty much
chocolate milk.

06:17.844 --> 06:19.377
Gimme that!
Whoa!

06:19.379 --> 06:21.646
Just sip it now,
you'll get brain freeze.

06:21.648 --> 06:23.248
Do I look like I care?!

06:23.250 --> 06:25.918
You're dealing with a man
who's got nothing to lose!

06:25.920 --> 06:28.120
[ gunshot ]
oh, god, brain freeze!

06:28.122 --> 06:30.255
Don't shoot!
Don't shoot!

06:30.257 --> 06:32.524
I'm so sorry to hear
that you were robbed.

06:32.526 --> 06:34.659
But what can you do
when a criminal mastermind

06:34.661 --> 06:35.794
Is on the loose?

06:35.796 --> 06:37.796
They took the only thing
of value

06:37.798 --> 06:39.998
In this poop-turd
of a life.

06:40.000 --> 06:41.800
Uh, how much value exactly?

06:41.802 --> 06:44.402
More than $500?
Less than $5,000?

06:44.404 --> 06:46.071
Can you give me
a ballpark here?

06:46.073 --> 06:48.607
My god!
They're selling it?

06:48.609 --> 06:51.676
Oh, oh,
who-gives-a-flip.

06:51.678 --> 06:53.612
That's what
I'm saying, too.

06:53.614 --> 06:56.481
I mean, whoever's selling it
ain't got no damn bids.

06:56.483 --> 06:57.816
Ain't got no looks.

06:57.818 --> 06:59.818
Hell, it ain't favorited
by no damn body.

06:59.820 --> 07:00.953
No.

07:00.955 --> 07:05.023
Who-gives-a-flip was
my character's name.

07:05.025 --> 07:06.825
It was the summer of '96,

07:06.827 --> 07:09.828
And atlanta was hosting
the olympics.

07:09.830 --> 07:12.564
I auditioned for the mascot
"whatizit,"

07:12.566 --> 07:15.167
Or izzy for short.

07:15.169 --> 07:17.169
But I'm afraid
I didn't get it.

07:17.171 --> 07:20.438
Let's just say white privilege
doesn't always come through

07:20.440 --> 07:23.175
When you're competing
against other whites.

07:23.177 --> 07:25.844
But they did have various
regional knock-offs --

07:25.846 --> 07:28.313
Whodatiz,
whatchamadiddle,

07:28.315 --> 07:29.848
And thingamajig.

07:29.850 --> 07:32.450
I landed the role
of who-gives-a-flip

07:32.452 --> 07:35.120
At the white water competition
in ducktown.

07:35.122 --> 07:36.989
♪ don't you remember?
Don't you know? ♪

07:36.991 --> 07:38.323
